The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 Sumana Sadhukhan, 25, was found hanging in her Bishnupur home, on the southern fringes of the city, on Wednesday morning. Police said her parents complained that Sumana, married two years ago to small-time trader Raja, was tortured regularly for dowry by her husband and in-laws. Raja was arrested and a hunt is on for his parents.

 Deepankar Dey Sarkar, 30, was found unconscious on the southern bank of Subhas Sarobar, in the Phoolbagan area, on Wednesday morning. He was a resident of Beleghata Main Road. He was taken to NRS Medical College and Hospital, where he was declared dead. A suicide note was found in his chest pocket.

 Ten-year-old pillion-rider Shahbaz Hussain sustained injuries on his legs on Wednesday morning when the motorcycle he was on was hit by a truck at the crossing of Chittaranjan Avenue and CIT Road, in Bowbazar. The truck was impounded but the driver fled. 

 Bikash Sinha, director, Saha Institute of Nuclear Physics and Variable Energy Cyclotron Centre, and Sushanta Dattagupta, director, Indian Institute of Science Education and Research, on Wednesday felicitated scientist C.N.R. Rao, Linus Pauling research professor and honorary president, Jawaharlal Nehru Centre for Advanced Scientific Research, Jakkur (Bangalore). Rao was recently conferred a doctor of science, honoris causa, of Oxford University.

 Nine pairs of Guwahati-Yeshwantpur weekly specials via Howrah will run from May 5 to July 2. The train will start every Saturday from Guwahati and every Monday from Yeshwantpur. 

 Bishnupada Das, 72, was found hanging in his Kashi Mitra Ghat Street home, in the Shyampukur area, on Tuesday evening. He was taken to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital, where he was declared dead. The body was sent for post-mortem.

